Description: Fragment of oal handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 87, 1? Name Symmachos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX F 169.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0904)
